# mstack mechanical pass

Use when the user marks work as **mechanical**, **chore**, **trivial**, or **quick patch**, or **@mentions** this rule.

## Posture

- **Think + Plan** in **3–5 lines** in chat (goal, files, verify command)—do **not** open `templates/PLAN_TEMPLATE.md` unless the user asks.
- **Build** with minimal diff; match repo style.
- Still follow **`mstack-token-discipline.mdc`** (narrow search, bounded reads).
- Still follow **`mstack-permissions.mdc`** — confirm before destructive git, filesystem, DB, or production ops.

## When **not** to use this rule

- **Security-sensitive** paths (auth, crypto, sessions, webhooks).
- **Schema / migrations** (`mstack-data-modeling.mdc`, `mstack-data-migrations.mdc`).
- **New user-facing behavior** or unclear product scope — use full **`mstack-core-workflow.mdc`** and optionally **`mstack-product-review.mdc`**.
- **Multi-file or cross-cutting** refactors without an agreed spec — use Plan Mode and normal Plan.

## Output

- Short summary of what changed and how to verify (one command if possible).
